        understand: "Explain why the membrane of a psychrophilic bacterium contains a higher proportion of unsaturated fatty acids compared to a mesophile growing at 37°C. Your explanation must connect membrane lipid composition to membrane fluidity and explain why fluidity is critical for cell function at low temperature.",
        apply:      "Taq polymerase from Thermus aquaticus has revolutionised molecular biology. (a) Identify the specific molecular property that makes it suitable for PCR that mesophilic polymerases lack. (b) Predict what would happen to PCR efficiency if a mesophilic DNA polymerase were substituted, with reference to the temperature profile of a standard PCR cycle. (c) Taq polymerase lacks 3'→5' proofreading activity. For which PCR application would this limitation be most problematic, and what alternative enzyme would you use?",
        analyze:    "An acidophilic bacterium maintains an internal pH of 6.8 despite growing in pH 1.5 external medium. This requires maintaining a transmembrane ΔpH of 5.3 pH units. Analyse: (a) what the direction and magnitude of the proton gradient implies about passive proton flow across the membrane; (b) what active mechanisms must be operating to maintain this gradient; (c) why this massive ΔpH is an opportunity as well as a challenge — specifically how this organism generates ATP from its pH gradient.",
        evaluate:   "Evaluate the biotechnological and commercial significance of extremophile research, using Taq polymerase and biomining as your two primary examples. For each: assess the scale of economic impact, identify the microbial ecological research that enabled the discovery, and evaluate whether the value generated justifies the cost of extremophile ecology fieldwork and bioprospecting as a research investment. Conclude with a reasoned position on whether extremophile research should receive increased public funding.",
        create:     "Design a directed evolution experiment to engineer an acidic cellulase (for use in biomass degradation at pH 4.5 in biofuel production) starting from a mesophilic cellulase that is optimally active at pH 7.0 and inactive below pH 5.5. Your design must specify: (a) the mutagenesis strategy (random vs site-directed) and justification; (b) the screening assay for pH 4.5 activity; (c) how many rounds of selection you would perform and what criteria would indicate success; (d) the structural analysis you would conduct on the evolved variant; (e) the trade-offs in activity or stability you would monitor to ensure the engineered enzyme remains practically useful."
