        analyze:    "A lacI⁻ lacO⁺ lacZ⁻ strain (chromosome) is made partially diploid with an F′ lacI⁺ lacO^c lacZ⁺ episome. Analyse the expression of lacZ in this merodiploid: (a) determine which lacZ gene (chromosomal or episomal) will be expressed; (b) determine whether expression is constitutive or regulated; (c) explain whether the lacI gene product acts in cis or trans and provide the evidence from this cross; (d) explain whether the operator acts in cis or trans and provide the evidence.",
